The paper deals with the problem of inferring information about events emerging in real life based on the contents of textual streams, specifically social media. This falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses statistical machine learning methods to analyze the data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with spatiotemporal characteristics of the data, which could fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.SD), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
